Externalized configuration

8Ô∏è‚É£ Starter Dependencies
Definition
Predefined dependency bundles that simplify dependency management.
Key Points
Reduce version conflicts

Examples:
spring-boot-starter-web
spring-boot-starter-data-jpa
spring-boot-starter-security
Can exclude unwanted dependencies

9Ô∏è‚É£ Auto Configuration
Definition:
Automatically configures Spring beans based on classpath, properties, and conditions.

Key Points:
Enabled by @EnableAutoConfiguration
Conditional annotations (@ConditionalOnClass)
Can be disabled or customized

üîü Application Properties / YML
Definition:
External configuration files for application behavior.

Key Points:
application.properties or application.yml
